      • getLastModifiedTime

        public long getLastModifiedTime()
        Description copied from class: File
        Get the last modified / last write timestamp of this file. Of the 3 file timestamps (created, modified, and accessed) on files, modified is most important in Windows. It's the one displayed by default with the "dir" command and shown in file details in Explorer. It's also the timestamp used for most other applications. So that's the timestamp that JSimple best supports querying and changing.
        Specified by:
        getLastModifiedTime in class File
        Returns:
        last modified timestamp for file

      • setLastModifiedTime

        public void setLastModifiedTime(long time)
        Description copied from class: File
        Set the last modified / last write timestamp of this file. Of the 3 file timestamps (created, modified, and accessed) on files, modified is most important in Windows. It's the one displayed by default with the "dir" command and shown in file details in Explorer. It's also the timestamp used for most other applications. So that's the timestamp that JSimple best supports querying and changing.
        Specified by:
        setLastModifiedTime in class File
        Parameters:
        time - time in millis (milliseconds since Jan 1, 1970 UTC)
